This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GAN) for data augmentation in machine learning tasks. It also involves experiments to evaluate the performance of GAN-based data augmentation, which is a common practice in machine learning research. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as GAN-based data augmentation is widely used in image-related tasks. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as these fields also involve machine learning and data augmentation techniques.
